-- Hungary Fiscal Head Jarai Quits, Kovacs Named as Successor: MTI
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-01-10T09:25:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/hungary-fiscal-head-jarai-quits-kovacs-named-as-successor-mti.html
Zsigmond Jarai, the president of
 Hungary ’s Fiscal Council, which has a right to veto the budget,
resigned, and was replaced by Arpad Kovacs, former head of the
country’s audit office, the state news service  MTI  said.  Jarai, who also serves as the head of the central bank’s
supervisory board, cited an increased workload, according to
MTI.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edith Balazs at 
